---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 62
  - Title: Cittavisuddhiprakarana
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Separation-Sin=The Extraction of Poison with Poison
  - Union-Identity=Mysterium Magnum=Non-Duality
---
Just as water that has entered the ear may be removed by water and just as a
thorn may be removed by a thorn, so those who know how, remove passion by
means of passion itself. Just as a washerman removes the grime from a
garment by means of grime, so the wise man renders himself free of impurity
by means of impurity itself.
